name: Elana James
text: Good service. Bad management. They owe copious amounts of money to ex employees. But hey, young kids can't afford legal representation so who cares right? Throw them under a bus. Teach em young that humans are scum. Management deserves to be fired. Love the pizza bites though.

name: Cody C
text: A guy working there overheard me mention that I had never had one of their pretzels, so he gave me a free sample. We came back after shopping some and got drinks and two types of pretzel bites. The girl who took our order was extremely nice and outgoing, a very bubbly personality. She also applied a coupon since we had forgot ours from earlier. The pizza bites and strawberry lemonade were delicious.

name: C Taylor
text: I have stop by this kiosk a few times and the pretzels weren't at all what I thought they would be. Terrible. Two young men, one of which I believe was type of management,  could careless about customers but more about flirting with young women. This last visit we were completely ignored. They were to busy with friends to bother with customers.  I could excuse his behavior bit when you walk up and they see you just to turn around and ignore your presence is to much. Worst of all,  someone is actually paying them to work and getting nothing in return.

name: Amanda Villarreal
text: I had a wonderfully vile experience here today. I visited and waited, and waited, until I asked the young girl behind the counter, who was eating and staring at me at the time, if they were open. After she said yes, I ordered. Out of cheese sauce. That’s ok, I finished my order and showed her my app in which I’d downloaded T-Mobile Tuesdays newest promo code. She said it’s not coming up, with no explanation. I told her since I pressed redeem I would lose the coupon now - nothing. I’ll pass up on this place next time, not worth it.
